       [TakeutiZaring] p. 30.  The epsilon relation and set membership are the
       same, that is, ` ( A _E B <-> A e. B ) ` when ` B ` is a set by
       ~ epelg .  Thus, 5 ` _E ` { 1 , 5 }.  (Contributed by NM,
       13-Aug-1995.) $)
    df-eprel $a |- _E = { <. x , y >. | x e. y } $.
  $}

